      section#rules
        h2 Rules for participation
          h5 Screening
          p The screening will be primarily based on your best hack link. We will also consider your previous open source contributions, so make sure you impress us with both the above. If selected, you will be given a notice a week in advance of the event.
          p <strong>Why do we screen?</strong>
          p Organizing a hackathon requires huge effort and comes at a great cost. It is obvious that we would want to maximize the value for our sponsors, which is having great hackers. 

          h5 Registration
          p To participate, fill in the <a href="#registration">registration form</a>. Last date for registration is 20th October, 2012. Please see that registrations are individual

          h5 Eligibility
          p You should be a student studying at a university/college somewhere. 

          h5 Theme
          p The theme of the hackathon will be declared shortly.

          h5 Team size
          p Based on the screening the team size will be decided. The maximum team size is limited to 3 team members. The teams will be made on the day of the hackathon.

          h5 Duration
          p This is a 24 hour hackday, starting 10:00 AM on Saturday, November 3<sup>rd</sup>, 2012.

          h5 Presentation
          p At the end of the hackday, each team has to present their hack to our judges in 10 minutes. You are required to prepare a short presentation and demo your hack. Only the work done during the hackathon can be presented. Any team presenting pre-existing work will be disqualified. Mention clearly what your hack is and if you have used pre-existing work.
